\nvaluations $(v^h, v^a)$ where\n\n$v^a$ is rank-$1$,\n$v^a$ is a vertical generalization of $v^h$.\n\nWarning: a trivial valuation is also regarded as a rank-$1$ valuation.\nBy definition, there are continuous maps $$ \\operatorname{Spo}(R, R^+) \\to\n\\operatorname{Spa}(R, R^+) \\to \\operatorname{Spec} R. $$\n","id":"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/math/olivine/","title":"The olivine spectrum"},"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/olivine-internal-graph/":{"body":"","id":"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/olivine-internal-graph/","title":"Graph"},"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/olivine-internal-sitemap/":{"body":"","id":"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/olivine-internal-sitemap/","title":"Sitemap"}},"docInfo":{"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/":{"body":0,"title":1},"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/dev/":{"body":0,"title":1},"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/dev/olivine/":{"body":7,"title":2},"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/journal/":{"body":0,"title":1},"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/journal/2023-08-03/":{"body":13,"title":3},"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/math/":{"body":0,"title":1},"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/math/olivine/":{"body":50,"title":2},"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/olivine-internal-graph/":{"body":0,"title":1},"https://dongryul-kim.github.io/olivine/olivine-internal-sitemap/":{"body":0,"title":1}},"length":9},"lang":"English"}